Redis-Tools is a collection of utilities for gathering information from running Redis instances, useful for gathering statistics on running Redis instances, load testing, and more.

-----

To Install:

  % make

Just Redis-Stat:

  % make redis-stat

Just Redis-Load:

  % make redis-load

Running:

  % ./redis-stat

 ------- data ------ ------------ load ----------------------------- - childs -
 keys      used-mem  clients blpops  requests            connections

Running:

  % ./redis-load

Example Output:

PRNG seed is: 4190317218 - use the 'seed' option to reproduce the same sequence
====== Report ======
  10006 requests completed in 0.35 seconds
  50 parallel clients
  1 min bytes payload
  64 max bytes payload
  keep alive: 1

